 Smart Campus Management System

 Modern universities manage large volumes of information every day,
 including student records, course registrations,
 library resources, hostel allocation, help desk, and event bookings.
 The performance of these systems depends heavily on the correct use of data structures.
 You are tasked in groups to design and implement a Smart Campus Management System using Java.
 The system will simulate how a university stores and processes campus data.
 The application must run as a menu-driven console program that allows users to interact with the system.
 The assignment aims to help students understand how different data structures solve different
 problems in real-world systems and to develop your skills in:

-Selecting appropriate data structures for specific problems

-Implementing custom data structures from scratch

-Designing modular, object-oriented systems

-Handling real-world data management challenges

